The paper proposes a cloud-based method for efficient analysis of large-scale newly arriving data, which involves designing compact data store and index structures, formulating a set of query operations, and optimizing performance using domain aware filter, accuracy aware data partition, highly efficient index, and frequently used statistical data designs. These techniques are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), distributed and parallel computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer engineering (cs.CE), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
